The thing with writing characters to show off their alien nature is that they still have to act human, or else they become unappealing. Ultimately any alien or fantasy race will always act like us with certain exaggerated traits because they need to be familiar in some sense.
Just because a story doesn't obsess over a characters otherworldly appearance and habits at every waking moment doesn't mean that the character doesn't benefit from their alien appearance. It seems like a relatively easy balance to strike, and it's best not to change a style of writing to match niche tastes.

Personally I thing BitS hits it right on the money, with the bug lady occasionally doing something with their anatomy to showcase its function, while also having her occasionally remark on the difference between her and the human.
